event.content:
Gas & Glaze Cars And Coffee is a new Saturday morning car meet in La Puente at Fresh Donuts.  And that’s located south of West Covina and north of Hacienda Heights.

The event started in March of 2021.  All types of cars, trucks, motorcycles, and creations are welcome.  And I highlight ‘creations’ because when I went I met Ed.  He’s pictured above with his semi-tractor.

Custom mini-semi-tractor next to a… ’60’s Chevelle – I think.

 

And, the picture is in no way altered.  Because Ed is standing next to his 100% homemade semi-tractor creation.  He even made the frame!  So it turns out Ed’s made a number of these creations.  Red, mini, totally custom, semi-tractors.  He’s a retired auto mechanic and is happy to talk about his truck.  Because he’s actually made four or five similar trucks!

Gas & Glaze C&C isn’t immediately off any surrounding highways but it’s easy to get to.  A SoCal native named Mike started the event.  And he’s committed to growing a regular crowd for the gathering.

Finally, I brought a couple of Fresh Donuts home for my toddler son and me to enjoy.  And we give their donut recipe two-thumbs-up each… so, four thumbs-up. :0)

Gas & Glaze Cars And Coffee – La Puente, California

Dates: Every Saturday morning
Location: Fresh Donuts, 560 Workman Mill Road, La Puente, CA 91746
Starts: 6 AM
Ends: 8 AM
Admission: Free
Vehicle Registration: Free

*Also, please note: iDriveSoCal does not host this event.  So if you’d like to learn more about the event please contact event organizers.  And that includes more specific details about attending, displaying your vehicle, and becoming a vendor or sponsor.

Additionally, for more of the best Southern California automotive events click HERE.

First-timer?  Review our Ultimate Guide to Cars And Coffee events and roll like a pro!

And, ever wonder how cars and coffee events got started?  Check out this podcast on The History Of Cars And Coffee!

Plus, if you have an event that you think we should post?  Contact us HERE.
